title: Ask HN: Stable Diffusion Course Topics?
text:
Thinking about creating a Stable Diffusion course, since trying to learn more about it and figure easiest way is to just try teach other people wanting to use it.

Any questions, suggestions, links to existing guides, support communities, etc.?

title: Ask HN: Open-source maintainers, how do you search for sponsors?
text:
I'm an open-source maintainer of a moderately popular developer tool. While I got sponsors from time to time, I would like to find more to sustain myself and dedicate more time to the project.
I tried to contact companies sponsoring other open-source projects through Twitter or by email but got no response most of the time.
I don't expect instant success, and I know that I am pretty average when it comes to marketing/sales.
But still, I would be curious to hear from other open-source maintainers and their strategies, if any.

Ask HN: Generalist contractors, what is your hourly rate?
text: There was a question a couple days ago about hourly rate, and a lot of the discussion revolved around raising compensation by specializing. Of course, generalists can still specialize, but it's a bit different. So, I'm curious what the answers will be like if we hear from only generalist developers.
